The Pushpa movies are a series of action dramas about a laborer who rises through the ranks of a red sandalwood smuggling syndicate: [1, 2, 3]  

Pushpa: The Rise 

The first installment in the series, released in 2021, follows Pushpa, a daily wager who rises through the ranks of a red sandalwood smuggling syndicate. The movie stars Allu Arjun as Pushpa, Rashmika Mandanna, Fahadh Faasil, Jagadeesh Prathap Bandari, Dhananjaya, Sunil, and Ajay Ghosh. [1, 2, 3]  

Pushpa 2: The Rule 

The sequel to Pushpa: The Rise, this movie features a 3-hour and 21-minute runtime. It includes sequences that echo the highlights of the first film, as well as new ones that show Pushpa still causing trouble for the police. [4]  

Pushpa 3 

The third installment in the series is expected to be released soon, with many scenes already shot.  


Some say that the Pushpa movies teach lessons about self-belief, hard work, determination, and the importance of strong relationships. Others say that the movies are riveting in some parts, but bland in others. [3, 6]  

